BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 3798.05 of the Revised Code be 4
enacted to read as follows: 5
Sec. 3798.05. (A) In utilizing an electronic health 6
records system to maintain the records of a patient who is a 7
minor, a health care provider shall ensure to the fullest extent 8
permitted under the HIPAA privacy rule and Ohio law that the 9
minor's parent or guardian has access in that system to the 10
minor's health records. This includes, if necessary to ensure 11
parent or guardian access to the fullest extent, maintaining the 12
minor's records in such a manner that separates records relating 13
to care that the minor received without parent or guardian 14
consent and care received with parent or guardian consent. 15
Additionally, a health care provider shall not require the 16
minor's parent or guardian to obtain the minor's authorization 17
before the parent or guardian may access in the electronic 18

