(B) A health care provider that maintains protected health 21
information for patients who are minors shall do both of the 22
following: 23
(1) Annually inform each minor's parent or guardian of 24
both of the following: 25
(a) Circumstances in which a minor is permitted under Ohio 26
law to receive health care without parent or guardian consent, 27
including under sections 2108.31, 2151.85, 2907.29, 3701.242, 28
3709.241, 3719.012, 5120.172, and 5122.04 of the Revised Code; 29
(b) That any medical records pertaining to care of a minor 30
patient consented to without parent or guardian consent may not 31
be disclosed to the parent or guardian unless the minor has 32
authorized the disclosure. 33
(2)(a) Except as provided in division (B)(2)(b) of this 34
section, at each minor's annual well visit, provide the minor an 35
opportunity to provide general, ongoing written consent for 36
parent or guardian access to the minor's medical records 37
regarding care that the minor patient may have consented to, or 38
may consent to in the future, without parent or guardian 39
consent. 40
(b) The requirement in division (B)(2)(a) of this section 41
does not apply if a minor provides written consent as described 42
under that division, and the minor has not revoked that consent. 43
Section 2. This act shall be known as the My Child-My 44
Chart Act. 45

